(158, 10, 177, 0, 'mmc-1630300794.jpg', 'The Executive, Accounts and Finance is responsible for preparing, maintaining, handling regular Cash / Bank management complying all rules and regulations of the company and government bodies so that the company will be able to achieve its desired objectives.', 'To prepare and maintain Vouchers, Cash / Bank Book, Stock Register, Fixed Assets Register etc. timely for smooth operation of accounting system. \r\nTo petty cash management, and reconcile everyday as per following company guidelines. \r\nTo operate day to day functional banking as per company policies and procedures.\r\nTo entry all receipt and payment in the software regularly.\r\nPrepare VAT Chalan according to the Govt rules and Regulations and submit to the reporting officer in due time for next course of action.To comply Tax/Custom Duty/Income Tax (if applicable) as per rules and regulations and submit report accordingly. \r\nTo prepare and submit daily/weekly/monthly/yearly report as per schedule date for smooth operation. \r\nEnsure necessary support to Accounts & Finance Department as or when required.\r\nAny other duties and responsibilities assigned by the management.', 0, 'Dhaka', 4, 0, 0, NULL, 'Mobile bill, Medical allowance, Provident fund, Insurance, Gratuity\r\nLunch Facilities: Partially Subsidize\r\nFestival Bonus: 2\r\nAs per standard rules and policies.', 1, '2021-08-30 05:19:54', '2021-08-30 05:19:54'),
(159, 10, 178, 1, 'mmc-1630301254.jpg', NULL, 'Candidates will have to provide tracking (FFL) support as per the operations need. \r\nHe will be responsible for memo checking and other jobs that are related to memo checking. \r\nCommunication with the Clients and Sales team. \r\nAny other jobs assigned by the management time to time as per company needs.', 0, 'Dhaka', 4, 0, 0, NULL, 'Salary increment after every 1.5 years based on good performance. \r\nLight meal will be served every day. \r\n2 Festival Bonus. \r\nOvertime Facility. \r\nMobile Bill. \r\nOther benefits as per company policy.', 1, '2021-08-30 05:27:34', '2021-08-30 05:27:34'),
(160, 11, 179, 0, 'mmc-group-1630301989.png', NULL, 'Perform all cash management/store management activities of different units of the company\r\nManage inventories and prepare cash book, ledger, bills/invoices and vouchers on daily basis\r\nMaintain and update ERP records timely and provide support in all other departmental activities\r\nTake any other assignment of the concerned section given by supervisor', 0, 'Dhaka', 4, 0, 0, '•	Depending upon the qualification, experience and profile of the candidate, remuneration will be competitive.', NULL, 1, '2021-08-30 05:39:49', '2021-08-30 05:39:49'),
(161, 11, 180, 0, 'mmc-group-1630302894.png', 'Duration of the Appointment initially: 01 (One year)\r\nExpected Starting Date: 01 August 2021', 'Analyze and ensure charging following all budget information and chart of accounts.\r\nPrepare, maintain & update books of accounts (Voucher, Cashbook, bank book, ledger, etc.).\r\nPreparation of monthly, quarterly, semi-annually, and yearly cash financial reports (Income expenditure reports, balance sheet, bank reconciliation, cash flow, etc.).\r\nMaintain the records and documents for Audit facilitation.\r\nAssume responsibility in general for the proper management of cash transfers and in particular ensuring disbursements, receipts, and custody of cash under the planned activities are in line with established guidelines; ensures appropriate internal control are in place.\r\nSupport to prepare Monthly and yearly fund request preparation.\r\nMaintain appropriate records, reports, and necessary documents relating to the cash transfer activities in the area. Provide a variety of statistical information as appropriate.\r\nEnsure payments to vendors for project activities.\r\nKeep tracking project expenses from inception to date for reporting.\r\nPrepare expense analysis and review with the program management team and provide feedback/recommendations on deviation.\r\nTrack advances and accrual for timely adjustment.\r\nMaintains administrative control records such as commitments and expenditures; initiate and process administrative action relating to travel arrangements, payments, procurements, and delivery of equipment, supplies of inventories.\r\nSet up, classify, and maintain appropriate files in the office. Ensure proper supplies of materials; manage office premises, vehicles, and inventories.\r\nMaintain store as per organizational and donor requirement.\r\nVendor enlistment and relevant contract preparation.\r\nProvide support to all staff in the district; manage entitlements and benefits, including travel claims, leave, etc. in line with approved budget.\r\nMaintain and Keep track of all assets purchased under the project.\r\nEnsure all financial documents are kept in a safe place as per the requirement of donor retention policy.\r\nEnsure compliance with government VAT & tax requirements.', 0, NULL, 4, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, 1, '2021-08-30 05:54:54', '2021-08-30 05:54:54'),
(162, 10, 181, 1, NULL, 'A group of companies` assurance offices is looking for a General Manager -Accounts & Audit who is responsible for the day-to-day aspects of the business`s accounts, finance & find out companies profit & loss of the concerned business unit as per the requirements of the organization.\r\nThis is a permanent job where candidates are expected to work for a longer duration to pursue their careers.', 'Formulate the Financial Audit every month.\r\nKeep all accurate records for daily transactions manually.\r\nMaintain the financial books of accounts and statements in compliance with the requirements of the related bodies- Auditors (internal & external), NBR (Tax purpose), and Vat authorities.\r\nMonitor import/export, L/C Finance.\r\nPrepare investment proposal and business case preparation and due diligence.\r\nAssess optimum/budgeted inventory level and ensure financial control in inventory management.\r\nMonitor the Receivable and Payable status of relevant entities from time to time.\r\nEstablish control over Fixed Assets and ensure Appropriate Fixed Assets Register in the Context of Financial Accounting.\r\nThe candidate must be self-motivated & can handle accounts-related work of the company.\r\nPerform any other duties as assigned by the management from time to time.', 0, 'Palton, Dhaka.', 0, 55000, 75000, 'Negotiable', 'As per company policy', 1, '2021-08-31 05:04:03', '2021-08-31 05:06:31'),
(163, 11, 182, 1, NULL, NULL, 'Receive and process credit customer applications from businesses\r\nChecking credit customer\'s establishment, verify reference and bank record of the credit application\r\nChecking credit customer\'s documents i.e. signature of owner, mortgaged documents, post dated cheques\r\nMaintaining all credit supply records and documents for all businesses\r\nTraveling to depot locations for monitoring credit customer\'s activities\r\nAssist central credit coding operation', 0, 'Dhaka', 0, 45000, 50000, NULL, 'As per Company system', 1, '2021-08-31 05:04:32', '2021-08-31 05:04:32'),
(164, 11, 183, 1, NULL, 'Christian Service Society (CSS) is a renowned national NGO having 2,100 employees. We are currently seeking for an experienced Director-HRM & PMEL who will be responsible for developing, managing and supervising policies/regulations related to employee functions and management as well as program planning, monitoring, evaluation and learning.', 'Oversee overall staff recruitment and selection process.\r\nSupervise all organizational HR issues including Compensation, Benefits, Attendance and Leave Management, Organization Development/ Process Improvement, HR Database Management, Performance & Career Management etc.\r\nEstablish harmonious relationship with employees to ensure their engagement and motivation.\r\nPrepare and validate job description of the employees.\r\nSupervise the process of yearly performance evaluation of all staff.\r\nCarry-out Training Need Assessment and accordingly prepare yearly training plan\r\nFollow-up the implementation of internal training courses of the organization as well as projects.\r\nManage the disciplinary action, resignation, dismissal, discharge and termination procedures & ensure proper record management of all disciplinary actions & grievance issues.\r\nEnsure compliance with the provisions of the Labor Act of Bangladesh in case of staff management.\r\nTime to time update and recommend new HRM policies and procedures.\r\nConduct staff awareness program (Foundation training, Gender, workplace safety etc.).\r\nLook after the final settlement process of the employees.\r\nPrepare and finalize different types of HRM & PMEL related reports.\r\nMaintain confidentiality of organizational information and documents.\r\nProvide assistance to International team in new project designing and planning.\r\nPrepare Monitoring & Evaluation yearly plan for all program/ projects.\r\nEnsure proper monitoring of the projects and programs in collaboration with respective Monitoring officer.\r\nLead PMEL team for conducting internal and external evaluation (baseline, midterm and end-line).\r\nEnsure quality of organizational monitoring and evaluation system by introducing new tools and techniques.\r\nArrange quarterly follow-up meeting for monitoring & evaluation follow-up and learning.\r\nCapture the learning and achievements through proper documentations and ensure the quality of all publications.\r\nEnsure compliances of CSS PMEL manual.\r\nProvide necessary feedback and support to projects for better performance based on monitoring and evaluation findings.', 0, 'Dhaka', 0, 75000, 85000, NULL, 'After being permanent upon successful completion of probation period (six months), other benefits will be offered as per the organizational policy i.e. provident fund, gratuity, festival bonus, yearly increment, staff insurance (kormi Bima), medical allowance (Kormi Sohayota Tohobil) etc.', 1, '2021-08-31 05:12:58', '2021-08-31 05:12:58'),
(165, 11, 184, 1, NULL, 'Experiences in company secretarial works of listed companies.', 'The candidate will have to ensure compliance requirements of Bangladesh Securities and Exchange Commission, Dhaka/Chittagong stock exchanges and RJSC for the listed companies.', 0, 'Barishal', 0, 100000, 120000, NULL, 'T/A, Mobile bill, Gratuity\r\nLunch Facilities: Partially Subsidize\r\nSalary Review: Yearly\r\nFestival Bonus: 2', 1, '2021-08-31 05:21:24', '2021-08-31 05:21:24'),
(166, 11, 185, 1, NULL, NULL, 'Accountable for the development and coordination of the company\'s internal auditing activities.\r\nDevelop and implement internal auditing policies, procedures, and program to reduce cost.\r\nReview of accounting procedures.\r\nSupervise, conduct, and report on the testing and adequacy of the company\'s internal controls over financial reporting.\r\nRecommend corrective action and suggest improvement.\r\nAny other responsibilities assigned by the management.', 0, 'Dhaka', 4, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, 1, '2021-08-31 05:27:40', '2021-08-31 05:27:40'),
